    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-11-30T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-11-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="168"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d168">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72/12428: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Sofia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Murphy</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sofia</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-11-30">November 30,
                            1918</date>.<lb/>[Received December 4—5:55 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>192. Situation Dobroudja improved. Roumanian troops withdrawn by order and
                    recrossed river. So far as can be ascertained no excesses and no damage.
                    Bulgarian civil administration will remain in charge railroads, posts and
                    telegraphs.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Murphy</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
